text: Misa Q'asa (Quechua misa table, q'asa mountain pass,Yachakuqkunapa Simi Qullqa - Qusqu Qullaw. Qhichwa Simipi (monolingual Quechua and bilingual Quechua- Spanish dictionary) literally "table mountain pass", Hispanicized spelling Mesa Jasa) is a mountain in the Andes of Peru, about high. It is located in the Ayacucho Region, Lucanas Province, on the border of the districts of Aucara and Cabana. Misa Q'asa lies west of Misa Urqu and northeast of the archaeological site of Usqunta. ==References== Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Ayacucho Region
title: Misa Q'asa
